text: Garmisch-Partenkirchen is a mountain resort town in Bavaria in southern Germany. It is the administrative centre of the district of Garmisch- Partenkirchen, in the Oberbayern region, and the district is on the border with Austria. Nearby is Germany's highest mountain, Zugspitze, at . The Olympic Winter Games were held here in 1936. ==References== ==Other websites== * gapa.de - official website Category:Towns in Bavaria Category:Ski areas and resorts in Germany Category:Garmisch-Partenkirchen (district)
